window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b> Audie Award Nominee, Literary Fiction, 2013</b> </p> <p><i>New York Times</i> best-selling author Stephen Harrigan lit up the publishing world with his Spur Award-winning <i>The Gates of the Alamo</i>. The remarkable follow-up to that acclaimed hit, <i>Remember Ben Clayton</i> further cements Harrigan’s place as a premier voice in American fiction. </p> <p>Exiled to Texas with his grown daughter, sculptor Francis “Gil” Gilheaney is commissioned to create a statue for a man who recently lost his son in World War I. But as work on the statue progresses, secrets slowly reveal themselves and Gil’s fragile family threads begin to fray.</p>"; 
